The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Melbourne July 18 (PTI): A New Delhi-based television reporter from the Australian Broadcasting Corporation has been arrested in Singapore on charges of drug trafficking.           
	Peter Lloyd, 41, could be sentenced to a maximum of 20 years and up to 15 cane lashes. He allegedly possessed the drug ice and his urine tested positive. He was taken into custody on Thursday night.                   
	 Dubai (PTI): An Indian expatriate in Qatar, who had to close his restaurant seven years back, has been stranded in the country unable to repay $ 54,900 as rent arrears. P. Aboo, 61, who is from Kerala, is involved in a legal battle with his landlord and has been forbidden from leaving the country.                   
	 Melbourne (PTI): Twenty-seven Indians who have gone missing after arriving in New Zealand have been warned they would be forcibly removed from the country if they violated the conditions in their visas that expire on August 5. Thirty-nine had gone missing but 12 of them met immigration officials on Thursday and said they would return to India. They had come under the pretext of meeting the Pope for the World Youth Day.                  
	 Jammu (PTI): At least 25 people, including three CRPF jawans, were injured on Thursday in a blast at Banihal bus stand on the Jammu-Srinagar national highway.                   
	 Dubai (PTI): An Indian man has been sentenced to three months imprisonment for attempting to bribe a government official. The carpenter had offered a bribe of $ 1,835 for his sons driving licence, who had failed the test 11 times, officials said.                   
	 Jalgaon (PTI): Two undertrials have been rearrested after they drugged three policemen and escaped while being taken from Madhya Pradesh to Aurangabad for a court appearance. The duo allegedly offered the policemen sweets laced with sedatives.                                                                                                                         
